The President of the United States spoke to reporters at Joint Base Andrews in Maryland. He mentioned that he was going to Philadelphia to celebrate his wedding anniversary. He also expressed his excitement about receiving endorsements from all the unions, which he said has never happened before. The President mentioned that businesspeople and unions are starting to work together more closely. He believes this is the beginning of a significant change in the economic balance. When asked about the upcoming campaign and the possibility of a nasty campaign, the President said it depends on who the nominee is. Regarding tensions with China, the President stated that China has some legitimate difficulties unrelated to the United States. He hopes to meet with President Xi in the future to discuss their differences and areas of cooperation. The President also commented on Ukraine's potential membership in NATO, saying that they need to meet the same standards as other member nations. On Russia's deployment of tactical nuclear weapons to Belarus, the President called it "totally irresponsible."